<task id="WKSP-031" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build WorkspaceHeader component with layout switcher dropdown</title>
    <phase>4</phase>
    <tags>shared-components, frontend, fluent-ui</tags>
    <estimated-effort>5h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>001, 003</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Create a WorkspaceHeader component featuring a Fluent UI v9 dropdown for switching between workspace layouts, with system/user grouping and actions for editing and creating layouts.</goal>
    <context>
      The workspace page needs a header bar that lets users switch between their saved workspace layouts
      and system-provided defaults. System workspaces are read-only (shown with a lock icon) while user
      workspaces are editable. The header also provides entry points to the Layout Wizard: a settings/gear
      button that opens edit mode for user layouts or Save As mode for system layouts, and a "+ New Workspace"
      option at the bottom of the dropdown.

      This component lives in LegalWorkspace since it is specific to workspace personalization behavior,
      though it uses Fluent UI v9 primitives and shared component patterns from ADR-021.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST use Fluent UI v9 components exclusively (Dropdown, Option, Divider, Button) per ADR-021
      - MUST support dark mode via Fluent v9 design tokens (no hard-coded colors)
      - System workspaces MUST appear first with a lock icon (LockClosed from @fluentui/react-icons)
      - User workspaces MUST appear after a Divider
      - "+ New Workspace" option MUST appear at the bottom of the dropdown
      - Settings button behavior: edit mode for user layouts, Save As mode for system layouts
      - Props interface: activeLayout, layouts[], onLayoutChange, onEditClick, onCreateClick
      - MUST NOT contain any API call logic — parent provides data and callbacks
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read ADR-021 for Fluent v9 component usage patterns and ADR-012 for shared component conventions. Review existing LegalWorkspace components for code style consistency.</step>
    <step id="2">Define the WorkspaceHeaderProps interface: activeLayout (WorkspaceLayoutSummary), layouts (WorkspaceLayoutSummary[]), onLayoutChange (id: string) => void, onEditClick (layout: WorkspaceLayoutSummary) => void, onCreateClick () => void.</step>
    <step id="3">Create the WorkspaceHeader component with a Fluent Dropdown displaying the active layout name as the selected value.</step>
    <step id="4">Populate dropdown options: system layouts first (each with LockClosed icon prefix), then a Divider, then user layouts, then a Divider, then "+ New Workspace" action item.</step>
    <step id="5">Add a settings gear IconButton (Settings24Regular) next to the dropdown. Wire onClick to call onEditClick(activeLayout) — the parent determines edit vs Save As based on layout.isSystem.</step>
    <step id="6">Style the header using Fluent v9 makeStyles with design tokens for spacing, ensuring dark mode compatibility. Layout: flex row, dropdown on left, gear button on right.</step>
    <step id="7">Export the component and its props interface from the LegalWorkspace components directory.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>WorkspaceHeader renders a Fluent v9 Dropdown showing the active layout name</criterion>
    <criterion>System layouts appear first with a lock icon, separated from user layouts by a Divider</criterion>
    <criterion>"+ New Workspace" option appears at the bottom and triggers onCreateClick</criterion>
    <criterion>Settings gear button is visible and calls onEditClick with the active layout</criterion>
    <criterion>Component renders correctly in both light and dark themes</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
